# Registration api

## Launch project

docker build -t registration/spring-boot-docker .
docker run -p 8080:8080 registration/spring-boot-docker

## API specification

Swagger available on http://localhost:8080/swagger-ui/index.html

### Create user [POST]

http://localhost:8080/private/api/users

+ Request (application/json)


{
 	"userName":"test",
	"birthday":"1988-10-10",
	"countryCode":"FR",
	"phoneNumber":"123456789",
	"gender":"M"
}

+ Response 201 (application/json)

	+ Body
		{
		 	"userName":"test",
			"birthday":"1988-10-10",
			"countryCode":"FR",
			"phoneNumber":"123456789",
			"gender":"M"
		}
		
		
### Get user [GET]

http://localhost:8080/private/api/users/{id}

+ Response 200 (application/json)

	+ Body
		{
		 	"userName":"test",
			"birthday":"1988-10-10",
			"countryCode":"FR",
			"phoneNumber":"123456789",
			"gender":"M"
		}
		



